-- Ghana Producer-Price Inflation Rate Falls to 18% in July
-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 2012-08-22T12:42:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-22/ghana-producer-price-inflation-rate-falls-to-18-in-july-1-.html
Producer-price inflation in  Ghana ,
the second-biggest  economy  in West  Africa , slowed to 18 percent
in July from 19.1 percent a month earlier.  Prices rose 0.7 percent in the month, Philomena Nyarko, an
official at the Ghana Statistical Service, told reporters today
in the capital, Accra.  Costs for makers of textiles, food and beverages, and
chemicals slowed in the month, Nyarko said. The manufacturing
rate declined to 20 percent in July from 21.9 percent a month
earlier, she said.  Mining and quarrying in Africaâ€™s second-biggest gold
producer recorded the highest increase of the groups, rising
20.3 percent from 19.5 percent in June, according to the
statistical service. Utilities climbed to 10.6 percent from 10.1
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
